<subSubSection id="72A1650E0A130924379BFAC9C485FAB0" pageId="3" pageNumber="425" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="3A0436850A130924379BFAC9C485FAB0" blockId="3.[151,1437,1337,1616]" pageId="3" pageNumber="425">
<emphasis id="08CFEA970A130924379BFAC9C74AFA9B" bold="true" box="[151,274,1337,1363]" pageId="3" pageNumber="425">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species resembles 
<taxonomicName id="FDBB4D060A130924352CFACBC486FA9C" authorityName="Li &amp; Song" authorityYear="2010" box="[544,734,1338,1364]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Phlogothamnus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="425" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="polymaculatus">
<emphasis id="08CFEA970A130924352CFACBC486FA9C" box="[544,734,1338,1364]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="425">P. polymaculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but can be distinguished from the latter by the thinner pygofer ventral process and style and more robust aedeagus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
